-- Jennifer Lawrence Wins Best Actress Oscar for ‘Silver Linings’
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2013-02-25T04:48:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-25/jennifer-lawrence-wins-best-actress-oscar-for-silver-linings-.html
Jennifer Lawrence won the Academy
Award for best actress for her portrayal of a troubled young
woman in Weinstein Co.’s “Silver Linings Playbook.”  The award was handed out today at the 85th Academy Awards
in Hollywood. “Silver Linings Playbook,” directed by David O.
Russell, looks at two misfits, played by Lawrence and  Bradley
Cooper , as they try to piece their lives back together.  The film was nominated for eight Oscars, including best
actor for Cooper and best supporting actor for  Robert De Niro .
Jacki Weaver, the character’s mother, was nominated for best
supporting actress.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  